Factions:
  - Name: Maurya Indians
    Description: Founded in 322 B.C. by Chandragupta Maurya, the Maurya Empire was
      the first to rule most of the Indian subcontinent, and was one of the
      largest and most populous empires of antiquity. Its military featured
      bowmen who used the long-range bamboo longbow, fierce female warriors,
      chariots, and thousands of armored war elephants. Its philosophers,
      especially the famous Acharya Chanakya, contributed to such varied fields
      such as economics, religion, diplomacy, warfare, and good governance.
      Under the rule of Ashoka the Great, the empire saw 40 years of peace,
      harmony, and prosperity.
    Technologies:
      - Name: Elephant Roundup
        History: .
        Description: Capture up to 5 Gaia elephants and garrison them in the Elephant
          Stables to gain up to a 25% bonus in cost and train time of elephant
          units.
      - Name: Archery Tradition
        History: India was a land of archery. The bulk of any Indian army was made up of
          highly skilled archers, armed with bamboo longbows.
        Description: Archer units firing rate +10% faster, train time reduced -25%, but
          health reduced -10%.
      - Name: Arthaśāstra
        History: Chanakya is traditionally identified as the author of the Arthashastra,
          or 'The Science of Prosperity', an extensive treatise on how best to
          govern a large kingdom.
        Description: Chanakya can research 4 unique technologies based upon the
          Arthashastra.
      - Name: Kṣhatriya Warrior Caste
        History: Chanakya is traditionally identified as the author of the Arthashastra,
          or 'The Science of Prosperity', an extensive treatise on how best to
          govern a large kingdom.
        Description: All Champions +20% health.
      - Name: Wootz Steel
        History: Secret steel working techniques give sword blades distinctive and
          beautiful markings. Not only that, but the steel's hardness is
          unparalleled.
        Description: All sword units +20% attack.
