CivBonuses:
  - Name: Emperor of Emperors.
    History: The Maurya Empire encompassed dozens of formerly independent kingdoms
      over an area of 5 million square kilometers, with a population of close to
      60 million people. The Maurya regents held the title Emperor of Emperors
      and commanded a standing army of 600,000 infantry, 9000 elephants, 8000
      chariots, and 30,000 cavalry, making it arguably the largest army of its
      time.
    Description: Mauryas have a +10% population cap bonus (i.e., 550 pop cap instead
      of the usual 500).
  - Name: Ksatradharma.
    History: Kshatriya or Kashtriya, meaning warrior, is one of the four varnas
      (social orders) in Hinduism. Traditionally Kshatriya constitute the
      military and ruling elite of the Vedic-Hindu social system outlined by the
      Vedas and the Laws of Manu. Ksatradharma eventually became to be known as
      the primary duty of war, or law of kings and warriors, which gave rise to
      the Kshatriya caste.
    Description: The Mauryas enjoy access to 4 champions.
  - Name: Elephant Tradition
    History: India is the land of the elephants. Elephant warfare originated in
      India and continued for millennia. It was also the source of elephants for
      the eastern Mediterranean. Indian kings were able to field large numbers
      of war elephants.
    Description: Elephants −30% training time.
  - Name: Wooden Walls.
    History: The Mauryas built their city walls out of wood, an abundant natural
      resource in India.
    Description: City Walls -50% build time, but also -25% health.
